><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Quad kite HG's?</span><hr size=1> Sitting here, can't connect to EQ for some odd reason, was speculating.  Can a 52 wizard quad kite HG's in Rathe Mountains using PoF and BoF?<br>
<br>
Problem I can think of is their speed.  Supposedly it's a bit slower than a SOW, but still slower than jboots, right?  Another problem could be terrain, but have SoTF for judging distance, but of course there's always the danger of unwanted adds.<br>
<br>
So what does everyone think, horrible idea?  Too hard?  Best way to make plat in EQ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaureusalaneur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aureusalaneur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/5/01 7:04:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad kite HG's?</span><hr size=1> Only problem is they are camped most of the time...  I doubt you'd be able to get more than 2 to kite at a time, max.<br>
<br>
I've thought about it before too...  it would be excellent cash.  Just waking up at 4 a.m. on a weekday just to test it out (so Rathe Mountains would be empty) was not worth it to me.<br>
<br>
Aureusalaneur Silvanitari<br>
53 Channeler - Veeshan`s Talons<br>
Luclin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/5/01 7:39:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad kite HG's?</span><hr size=1> its doable at 49 if ur careful, dont ask me how he did it but i saw a lvl 50 wizard quadding hill giants.<br>
<br>
i wasnt brave enough until i was lvl 51 and got my first pillar spell. its a piece of cake as long as u can find 4 to round up. druids on the rathe pull em a millisecond after they pop. <br>
<br>
ive done it when the server had just come back up, you can really make cash fast this way<br>
<br>
Ulkesh Naranek<br>
56 Evoker (ie. Port Bitz)<br>
The Rathe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorsmoxlorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 10:36:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hg?</span><hr size=1> Are the HG in rathe any richer than the giants in the DL?  The terrian and the space is much more suited to quad kiting giants in the DL.  They seem to drop up to 5-6 plat a whack and some of the items they drop go to merchants for up to 50-60 plat.(tunics).  Just wondering?  I tried the HG for a day when I got my J-boots and the terrian was hard and trying to kite around everyone made it really annoying.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts??<br>
Orsmo Xlorr<br>
45 lvl Wizard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 10:46:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hg?</span><hr size=1> &gt;Are the HG in rathe any richer than the giants in the DL<br>
<br>
Yes, by quite a lot. Can drop up to around 40pp in just cash. <p>Qaman<BR>
Sorcerer - Eternal Wrath<BR>
Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 10:50:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hg?</span><hr size=1> rathe mtn giants usually drop a max of 50 plat, usually gold though, and fs weapons, the maximum loot from a hg could possibly be around 60 plat per kill, but they also sometimes only drop a cpl plat. ive even gotten 45 plat in silver from a hill giant. that was a mean trick hehe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubicrius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bicrius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 11:02:51 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://students.hamilton.edu/2002/bschulte/eqpics/bic_gin_sm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hg?</span><hr size=1> Quadding HG's in RM could be problematic post 50, ONLY because they're going to be getting green, and it'll only be good for putting some fast pp in your pocket.<br>
<br>
As for whether or not it's doable, they only have around 2200hp's, so do the math. Yes, they're quite doable, and VERY easy to round up. If you've ever soloed there, you'll know that there are some very good kiting alleys. I soloed there from 40 on up on and off, and found some amazing kiting alleys where the risk for adds is nill but it's possible you might run into groups of high 30's people hunting there... you'll have to scout it out first.<br>
<br>
As for RM giants being richer than DL giants? They're TONS richer. If you want to make straight pp there are no better and easier mobs than old world hill giants, especially RM hill giants.<br>
<br>
But If you think you're going to quad them for exp at 50+, think again... when I was 30 a 30 druid worked with me and we were taking down hill giants as a pair. Grantid, we're the only people I've ever known of to be able to do this, but level 50 people getting exp off mobs that are killable by level 30's? Not going to happen. Last time I went there I got no exp at all. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://elementsofpower.20m.com"><IMG SRC="http://webster.ij.net/~eop/shots/newbicsig2.gif" ALT="GIMME A BEER!!  I'll give you 40pp and a staff of writhing for some BEER!!" WIDTH=337 HEIGHT=150 BORDER=0 ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udanenel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danenel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 11:40:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hg?</span><hr size=1> I was getting minor exp in Rathe Mts last night at level 50. I'd say 30% still con blue... go figure. I did see a 51 wiz multi-kite 2 giants once while waiting for a guildmate.<br>
